propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propDefaultValue: The default value. Use when the component is not controlled.
propEmptyIcon: The icon to display when empty.
propEmptyLabelText: The label read when the rating input is empty.
propGetLabelText:
Accepts a function which returns a string value that provides a user-friendly name for the current value of the rating.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propName:
The name attribute of the radio `input` elements.
This input `name` should be unique within the page.
Being unique within a form is insufficient since the `name` is used to generated IDs.
propOnChange: Callback fired when the value changes.
propOnChangeActive: Callback function that is fired when the hover state changes.
propPrecision: The minimum increment value change allowed.
propReadOnly: Removes all hover effects and pointer events.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesSizeSmall: Styles applied to the root element if `size="small"`.
stylesSizeLarge: Styles applied to the root element if `size="large"`.
stylesReadOnly: Styles applied to the root element if `readOnly={true}`.
stylesDisabled: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if `disabled={true}`.
stylesFocusVisible: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if keyboard focused.
stylesLabel: Styles applied to the label elements.
stylesLabelEmptyValueActive: Styles applied to the label of the "no value" input when it is active.
stylesIcon: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements.
stylesIconEmpty: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when empty.
stylesIconFilled: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when filled.
stylesIconHover: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when hover.
stylesIconFocus: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when focus.
stylesIconActive: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when active.
stylesDecimal: Styles applied to the icon wrapping elements when decimals are necessary.
